<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Oil System Module Assembly and Secondary
        Filtration - Installation - Oil System Module
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="3">
        <title>Oil System Module</title>
        <figure id="f2651018" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh13/H13022.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil and coolant seal locations</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Coolant seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil seal</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position oil and coolant gasket seals onto the oil cooler housing and begin working the
                seals into the seal recesses at intersections and mid-points. Do not work the seal from one end to the
                other, or seal may stretch resulting in difficult installation.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Ensure that the machined surface of the crankcase is clean and free of debris, old seals or
                damage that could affect the new seals of the oil system module.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position oil system module onto the crankcase mounting surface and install eight mounting
                bolts (M8 x 20). Tighten these bolts to the
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_219.xml" xrefid="t2651002" appearance="hottext">special torque value</hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651019" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh13/H13035.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil system module and secondary filter assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil system module assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 30 (8)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hose, 1 in O.D.</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hose clamp (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Secondary filtration filter assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 25 (6)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil cooler drain tube assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Support bracket bolt, M8 x 16</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 20 (8)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter (spin-on)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure a new O-ring has been installed onto the oil cooler drain tube. Slide tube into
                front side of oil cooler and position a support bracket bolt (M8 x 16) through bracket and into
                crankcase. Torque both oil cooler drain tube bracket bolts to the
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_219.xml" xrefid="t2651002" appearance="hottext">special torque value</hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f26510220" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh13/H13026.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing oil supply tube</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the oil supply tube fitting to the filter header. Tighten nut on the tube to the
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_219.xml" xrefid="t2651002" appearance="hottext">special torque value</hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fill oil filter with the proper grade and viscosity of engine oil, refer to the DT 466, DT
                570 and HT 570 Engine Operation and Maintenance Manual.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate new oil filter gasket with clean engine oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Spin oil filter onto header until the gasket initially makes contact. Using an oil filter
                wrench with a band width of 38 mm (1.5 in) or greater, tighten filter an additional 1 full turn.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Do not overtighten filter. A damaged filter may fracture or leak.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil pan drain plug (M18).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Refill cooling system.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
